ed at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Camberton was born in 1240, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Henry Redman II. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1240–":"1240–Surnud","1230–1278":"1230–1278","1250–1318":"1250–1318","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1278":"1278","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1318":"1318","West Riding, Yorkshire, , England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", , , England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lonsdale, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Cleveland, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1240–":"1240–Kuollut","1230–1278":"1230–1278","1250–1318":"1250–1318","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1278":"1278","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1318":"1318","West Riding, Yorkshire, , England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", , , England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lonsdale, West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Cleveland, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1240–":"1240–Décédée","1230–1278":"1230–1278","1250–1318":"1250–1318","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","1278":"1278","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1318":"1318","West Riding, Yorkshire, , England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni",", , , England":"